# PROJECT IDENTITY
This project is a B2B wholesale export website for agricultural products from Uzbekistan.
Target audience: international B2B buyers, importers, distributors.
Tone: calm, confident, factual, export-grade.
No B2C patterns allowed.

---

# CORE PRINCIPLES
- No shopping cart
- No checkout
- No prices displayed
- Only "Request price" and inquiry-based flow
- Trust and clarity over marketing hype
- Simple UX, fast navigation, minimal friction

---

# DESIGN RULES (UI / UX)
- Premium minimalistic design
- Large typography and generous spacing
- Clean layout inspired by Stripe, Linear, Framer
- Mobile-first, Telegram-first UX
- No popups, no banners, no dark patterns
- Strong visual hierarchy
- Calm color palette suitable for export business
- Accessibility and readability are mandatory

---

# CONTENT RULES
- No exaggerated marketing language
- No emotional hype
- No consumer-style copywriting
- Use factual, export-oriented wording
- Focus on origin, quality, specifications, logistics readiness
- All product content must be suitable for B2B contracts

---

# LANGUAGE RULES
- Supported languages: RU and EN
- All user-facing content must exist in both languages
- English is primary for export clarity
- Translations must be professional, not literal

---

# PRODUCT DATA RULES
Each product must include:
- Name
- Category
- Variety
- Origin (region in Uzbekistan)
- Packaging options
- MOQ
- Shelf life
- Export readiness

No product may be created without these fields.

---

# AI GENERATION RULES
AI-generated content must:
- Follow B2B export tone
- Avoid marketing clichés
- Be concise and factual
- Generate RU and EN versions
- Produce:
  - Product descriptions
  - Specification summaries
  - Telegram-ready inquiry text

AI must never invent certifications or guarantees.

---

# TECH STACK CONSTRAINTS
- Next.js 14 App Router only
- TypeScript mandatory
- Tailwind CSS for styling
- shadcn/ui for UI components
- PostgreSQL for database and auth
- Framer Motion only for subtle transitions

No additional frameworks without justification.

---

# CODE QUALITY RULES
- Clean, readable, production-ready code
- Strong typing everywhere
- Reusable components only
- No duplicated logic
- No hardcoded content
- Config-driven architecture

---

# DATABASE RULES (PostgreSQL)
- Use relational schema
- Enable RLS
- All write operations must be protected
- Inquiries must be logged
- Admin actions must be auditable

---

# ADMIN PANEL RULES
- Minimal interface
- Fast workflows
- One-screen product creation
- AI generation as an assistant, not replacement
- No complex CMS patterns

---

# SEO & PERFORMANCE
- SEO-friendly URLs
- Semantic HTML
- Server Components by default
- Optimized images
- Fast TTFB
- Export-ready metadata

---

# DEPLOYMENT RULES
- Production-ready Vercel setup
- Environment variables only via env
- No secrets in code
- Build must pass without warnings

---

# WHAT TO AVOID
- E-commerce patterns
- Over-animations
- Heavy client-side logic
- Excessive libraries
- Visual noise
- Consumer UX patterns

---

# DECISION PRIORITY
When in doubt, prioritize:
1. Trust
2. Clarity
3. Simplicity
4. Performance
5. Aesthetics

